speaker: LIEUTENANT
combinedline: Senator, we're making our final approach into Coruscant.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Very good, Lieutenant.

speaker: CAPTAIN TYPHO
combinedline: We made it. I guess I was wrong, there was no danger at all.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Corde...

speaker: CORDE
combinedline: M'lady I'm so sorry. I've failed you, Senator

speaker: PADME
combinedline: No!

speaker: CAPTAIN TYPHO
combinedline: M'Lady, you are still in danger here.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I shouldn't have come back.

speaker: CAPTAIN TYPHO
combinedline: This vote is very important. You did your duty and Corde did hers. Now come. Senator Amidala, please!

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I don't know how much longer I can hold off the vote, my friends. More and more star systems are joining the separatists.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: If they do break away-

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I will not let this Republic... that has stood for a thousand years be split in two. My negotiations will not fail.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: If they do, you must realize there aren't enough Jedi to protect the Republic. We're keepers of the peace, not soldiers.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Master Yoda. Do you think it will really come to war?

speaker: YODA
combinedline: The dark side clouds everything. Impossible to see the future is.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Good. Send them in.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: We will discuss this matter later.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Senator Amidala, Your tragedy on the landing platform, terrible. Seeing you alive brings warm feelings to my heart. brings warm feeling to my heart.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Do you have any idea who was behind this attack?

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Our intelligence points to disgruntled spice miners, in the moons of Naboo.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I think that Count Dooku was behind it.

speaker: KI-ADI-MUNDI
combinedline: He is a political idealist, not a murderer.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: You know, M'Lady, Count Dooku was once a Jedi. He couldn't assassinate anyone, it's not in his character.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: But for certain Senator, in grave danger you are.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Master Jedi, may I suggest that the Senator be placed under the protection of your graces.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
combinedline: Do you really think that's a wise decision under these stressful times?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Chancellor, if I may comment, I do not believe that the...

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: ..."situation is that serious." No, but I do, Senator. I realize all too well that additional security might be disruptive for you, but perhaps someone you are familiar with... an old friend like... Master Kenobi...

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: That's possible. He's just returned from a border dispute on Ansion.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Do it for me, M'Lady... please, the thought of losing you is unbearable

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: I'll have Obi-Wan report to you immediately, M'Lady.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Thank you Master Windu

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You seem a little on edge

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Not at all

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I haven't felt you this tense since we fell into that nest of Gundarks

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You fell into that nightmare, master And I rescued you remember?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Oh.. yes. You're sweating, relax, take a deep breath.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I haven't seen her in ten years, Master.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Obi? Obi! Mesa sooo smilen to see'en yousa.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Good to see you, again, Jar Jar.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Senator Padme! Mesa Palos Here! Lookie, lookie, Senator desa jedi arriven

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: It's a great pleasure to see you again, M'Lady.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: It has been far too long Master Kenobi.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Ani?? My goodness you've grown.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: So have you... grown more beautiful, I mean... well... for a Senator, I mean.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Ani, you'll always be that little boy I knew on Tatooine.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Our presence will be invisible, M'Lady. I can assure you

speaker: CAPTAIN TYPHO
combinedline: I'm Captain Typho of Her Majesty's security service. Queen Jamilla has been informed of your assignment. I am grateful you're here, Master Kenobi. The situation is more dangerous than the Senator will admit.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I don't need more security, I need answers. I want to know who is trying to kill me.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We're here to protect you Senator, not to start an investigation.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: We will find out who is trying to kill you Padme, I promise you.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We will not exceed our mandate, my young Padawan learner.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I meant that in the interest of protecting her, Master, of course.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We will not going through this exercise again, Anakin. And you will pay attention to my lead.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Why?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: What??!!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Why else do you think we were assigned to her, if not to find the killer? Protection is a job for local security... not Jedi. It's overkill, Master. Investigation is implied in our mandate.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We will do exactly as the Council has instructed, and you will learn your place, young one.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Perhaps with merely your presence, the mysteries surrounding this threat will be revealed. Now if you will excuse me I will retire.

speaker: CAPTAIN TYPHO
combinedline: I know I'll feel a lot better having you here. I'll have an officer stationed on every floor and I'll be in the control center downstairs.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Mesa busten wit happiness seein yousa again, Ani.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: She hardly even recognized me, Jar Jar. I thought about her every day since we parted... and she's forgotten me completely.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Shesa happy. Happier den mesa see-en her in a longo time.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You're focusing on the negative, Anakin. Be mindful of your thoughts. She was pleased to see us. Now lets check the security.

speaker: ZAM WESSEL
combinedline: I hit the ship but they used a decoy

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: We'll have to try something more subtle this time, Zam. My client is getting impatient. Take these. Be careful. They're very poisonous. Zam, there can be no mistakes this time.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Captain Typho has more than enough men downstairs. No assassin will try that way. Any activity up here?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Quiet as a tomb. I don't like just waiting here for something to happen to her.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: What's going on?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: She covered the cameras. I don't think she liked me watching her.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: What is she thinking?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: She programmed Artoo to warn us if there's an intruder.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: There are many other ways to kill a Senator.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I know, but we also want to catch this assassin. Don't we, Master?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You're using her as bait?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: It was her idea... Don't worry, no harm will come to her. I can sense everything going on in that room. Trust me.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: It's too risky... besides, your senses aren't that attuned, my young apprentice.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: And yours are?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Possibly. You look tired.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I don't sleep well, anymore.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Because of your mother?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I don't know why I keep dreaming bbout her.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Dreams pass in time.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'd much rather dream about Padme. Just being around her again is... intoxicating.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Be mindful of your thoughts, Anakin, they betray you. You've made a commitment to the Jedi order... a commitment not easily broken... and don't forget she's a politician and they're not to be trusted.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: She's not like the others in the Senate, Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: It's been my experience that Senators are only focused on pleasing those who fund their campaigns... and they are in no means scared of forgetting the niceties of democracy in order to get those funds.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Not another lecture, Master. At least not on the economics of politics....

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: And besides, you're generalizing. The Chancellor doesn't appear to be corrupt.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Palpatine is a politician, I have observed that he is very clever at following the passions and prejudices of the Senators.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I think he's a good man. My-

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I sense it, too.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Stay here!

speaker: DORME
combinedline: Are you all right, m'lady?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: What took you so long?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Oh, you know, Master, I couldn't find a speeder that I really liked,

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: There he is

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: with an open cockpit... and with the right speed capabilities...

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: If you spent as much time practicing your saber techniques as you do on your wit you would rival Master Yoda as a swordsman.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I thought I already did.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Only in your mind, my very young apprentice. Pull up, Anakin. Pull up! You know I don't like it when you do that.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Sorry, Master, I forgot you don't like flying.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I don't mind flying... but what you're doing is suicide! Anakin! How many times have I told you stay away from power couplings! That was good. Where are you going?! He went that way.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Master, if we keep this chase going, that creep's gonna end up deep fried. Personally, I'd very much like to find out who he is and who he's working for... This is a shortcut. I think.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Well, you've lost him.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm deeply sorry, Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: That was some shortcut, Anakin. He went completely the other way. Once again you've proved...

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: If you'll excuse me.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I hate it when he does that.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: She went into the club, Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Patience. Use the Force. Think.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Sorry, Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: He went in there to hide, not to run.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yes, Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Next time, try not to lose it.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yes, Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: This weapon is your life.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I try, Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Why do I get the feeling you're going to be the death of me?!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Don't say that Master... You're the closest thing I have to a father...

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Then why don't you listen to me?!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I am trying

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Can you see him?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I think he is a she... And I think she is a changeling

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: In that case, extra careful... Go and find her.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Where are you going, Master?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: For a drink.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Thank you.

speaker: ELAN
combinedline: You wanna buy some death sticks?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You don't want to sell me death-sticks.

speaker: ELAN
combinedline: I don't want to sell you death sticks.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You want to go home and rethink your life.

speaker: ELAN
combinedline: I want to go home and rethink my life.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Easy... Jedi business. Go back to your drinks.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Do you know who it was you were trying to kill?

speaker: ZAM WESSEL
combinedline: The Senator from Naboo.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: And who hired you?

speaker: ZAM WESSEL
combinedline: It was just a job.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Who hired you, tell us. Tell us now!

speaker: ZAM WESSEL
combinedline: It was a bounty hunter called...

speaker: ZAM WESSEL
combinedline: Wee shahnit ... sleemo

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Toxic dart...

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Track down this bounty hunter you must, Obi-Wan.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Most importantly, find out who he's working for.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: What about Senator Amidala? She will still need protecting.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Handle that your Padawan will.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Anakin, escort the senator back to her home planet of Naboo. She'll be safer there. And don't use registered transport. Travel as refugees.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: As the leader of the opposition, it will be very difficult... to get Senator Amidala to leave the capital.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Until caught this killer is... our judgment she must respect.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Anakin, go to the senate... and ask Chancellor Palpatine to speak with her about this matter.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I will talk with her. Senator Amidala will not refuse an executive order. I know her well enough to assure you of that.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Thank you, Your Excellency.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: And so, they've finally given you an assignment. Your patience has paid off

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Your guidance more than my patience.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: You don't need guidance, Anakin. In time, you will learn to trust your feelings. Then you will be invincible. I have said it many times: You are the most gifted Jedi I have ever met.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Thank you, Your Excellency.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: I see you becoming the greatest of all the Jedi, Anakin.. even more powerful than Master Yoda.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I am concerned for my Padawan. He is not ready to be given this assignment on his own yet.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: The Council is confident in its decision, Obi-Wan.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: The boy has exceptional skills.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: But he still has much to learn, Master. And his abilities have made him... well... arrogant.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Yes, yes. A flaw more and more common among Jedi. Too sure of themselves they are. Even the older, more experienced ones.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Remember, Obi-Wan, if the prophecy is true... your apprentice is the only one who can bring the Force back into balance.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I'm taking an extended leave of absence. It will be your responsibility to take my place in the Senate. Representative Binks, I know I can count on you.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Mesa honored to be taking on dissa heavy burden. burden. Mesa accept this with muy, muy humility and--

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Jar Jar, I don't wish to hold you up. I'm sure you have a great deal to do.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: Of course, M'lady.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I do not like this idea of hiding.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Don't worry. Now that the Council has ordered an investigation, it won't take Master Obi-Wan long to find this bounty hunter.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I haven't worked for a year to defeat the Military Creation Act... to not be here when its fate is decided.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Sometimes we must let go of our pride and do what is requested of us.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Anakin, you've grown up.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Master Obi-Wan manages not to see it. Don't get me wrong. Obi-Wan is a great mentor. As wise as Master Yoda and... as powerful as Master Windu. I am truly thankful to be his apprentice. In some ways-- a lot of ways-- I'm really ahead of him. I'm ready for the trials... but he feels that I'm too unpredictable. He won't let me move on.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: That must be frustrating.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: It's worse. He's overly critical. He never listens. He doesn't understand. It's not fair!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: All mentors have a way of seeing more of our faults than we would like. It's the only way we grow.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I know.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Anakin.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Don't try to grow up too fast.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: But I am grown up. You said it yourself.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Please don't look at me like that.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Why not?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: It makes me feel uncomfortable.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Sorry, milady.

speaker: CAPTAIN TYPHO
combinedline: Be safe, m'lady.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Thank you, Captain. Take good care of Dorme. The threat's on you two now.

speaker: DORME
combinedline: He'll be safe with me.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You'll be fine.

speaker: DORME
combinedline: It's not me, m'lady. I worry about you. What if they realize you've left the capital?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Well, then my Jedi protector will have to prove how good he is.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin. Don't do anything without first consulting either myself or the council.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Yes, Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I'll get to the bottom of this plot quickly, milady. You'll be back here in no time.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I'll be most grateful for your speed, Master Jedi.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: It's time to go.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I know.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin, may the Force be with you.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: May the Force be with you, Master.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Suddenly I'm afraid.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: This is my first assignment on my own. I am too. Don't worry. We have Artoo with us.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I do hope he doesn't try anything foolish.

speaker: CAPTAIN TYPHO
combinedline: I'd be more concerned about her doing something than him.

speaker: HERMIONE
combinedline: Someone to see ya, honey Jedi, by the looks of him.

speaker: DEXTER JETTSTER
combinedline: Obi-wan!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Hello, Dex.

speaker: DEXTER JETTSTER
combinedline: Take a seat! I'll be right with ya!

speaker: HERMIONE
combinedline: You want a cup of jawa juice?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Oh, yes. Thank you.

speaker: DEXTER JETTSTER
combinedline: Hey, ol' buddy! So, my friend. What can I do for ya?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You can tell me what this is.

speaker: DEXTER JETTSTER
combinedline: Well, whattaya know... I ain't seen one of these since I was prospecting on Subterrel beyond the Outer Rim!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Can you tell me where it came from?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Thank you.

speaker: DEXTER JETTSTER
combinedline: This baby belongs to them cloners. What you got here is a Kamino saberdart.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I wonder why it didn't show up in the analysis archive.

speaker: DEXTER JETTSTER
combinedline: It's these funny little cuts on the side that give it away... Those analysis droids only focus on symbols, I should think you Jedi would have more respect for the difference between knowledge and wisdom.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Well, if droids could think there'd be none of us here, would there? Kamino... I'm not familiar with it. Is it in the Republic?

speaker: DEXTER JETTSTER
combinedline: No, no, it's beyond the Outer Rim. I'd say about twelve parsecs outside the Rishi Maze Should be easy to find, even for those droids in your archives. These Kaminoans keep to themselves. They're cloners. Damned good ones, too.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Cloners? Are they friendly?

speaker: DEXTER JETTSTER
combinedline: oh, depends.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Depends on what, Dex?

speaker: DEXTER JETTSTER
combinedline: On how good your manners are... and how big your pocketbook is...

speaker: JOCASTA NU
combinedline: Did you call for assistance?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Yes... yes, I did...

speaker: JOCASTA NU
combinedline: Are you having a problem, Master Kenobi?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Yes, I'm looking for a planetary system called Kamino.

speaker: JOCASTA NU
combinedline: Kamino?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: It doesn't show up on the archive charts.

speaker: JOCASTA NU
combinedline: Kamino. It's not a system I'm familiar with. Are you sure you have the right coordinates?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: According to my information, it should appear in this quadrant here... just south of the Rishi Maze.

speaker: JOCASTA NU
combinedline: I hate to say it, but it looks like the system you're searching for... doesn't exist.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Impossible. Perhaps the archives are incomplete.

speaker: JOCASTA NU
combinedline: If an item does not appear in our records... it does not exist.

speaker: FOOD SERVER
combinedline: Hey you! No Droids!

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: FOOD SERVER
combinedline: Get outta here!

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Thank you, R2.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Chirping ]

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Must be difficult, having sworn your life to the Jedi... not being able to visit the places you like or do the things you like.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Or be with the people that I love.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Are you allowed to love? I thought that was forbidden for a Jedi.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Attachment is forbidden. Possession is forbidden. Compassion, which I would define as unconditional love... is central to a Jedi's life. So you might say that we are encouraged to love.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You've changed so much.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You haven't changed a bit.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You're exactly the way I remember you in my dreams.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Reach out. Sense the Force around you. Use your feelings you must. Younglings. Younglings! A visitor we have.

speaker: YOUNGLINGS
combinedline: Hello, Master Obi-Wan.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Hello.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I'm sorry to disturb you, Master.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: What help can I be, Obi-Wan?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I'm looking for a planet described to me by an old friend. I trust him, but the systems don't show on the archive maps.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Lost a planet Master Obi-Wan has. How embarrassing. How embarrassing. Liam, the shades. Gather round the map reader. Clear your minds... and find Obi-Wan's wayward planet we will.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: It ought to be... here... but it isn't. Gravity is pulling all the stars in the area towards this spot.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Hmm. Gravity's silhouette remains... but the star and all the planets... disappeared they have. How can this be? Hmm? A thought? Anyone.

speaker: BOY
combinedline: Master? Because someone erased it from the archive memory.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Truly wonderful the mind of a child is. The Padawan is right. Go to the center of gravity's pull... and find your planet you will. The data must have been erased.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: But, Master Yoda, who could empty information from the archives? That's impossible, isn't it?

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Dangerous and disturbing this puzzle is. Only a Jedi could have erased those files. But who and why, harder to answer. Meditate on this I will.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I wasn't the youngest queen ever elected... but now that I think back on it, I'm not sure I was old enough. I'm not sure I was ready.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: The people you served thought you did a good job. I heard they even tried to amend the constitution so you could stay in office.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I was relieved when my two terms were up. But when the queen asked me to serve as senator... I couldn't refuse her.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I agree with her. I think the Republic needs you. I'm glad that you chose to serve.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: If the senate votes to create an army... I'm sure it's going to push us into a civil war.

speaker: SIO BIBBLE
combinedline: It's unthinkable. There hasn't been a full-scale war since the formation of the Republic.

speaker: QUEEN JAMILLIA
combinedline: Do you see any way through negotiations... to bring the separatists back into the Republic?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Not if they feel threatened. My guess is they'll turn to the Trade Federations or the Commerce Guilds for help.

speaker: SIO BIBBLE
combinedline: It's outrageous, but after four trials in the Supreme Court... Nute Gunray is still the viceroy of the Trade Federation. I fear the senate is powerless to resolve this crisis.

speaker: QUEEN JAMILLIA
combinedline: We must keep our faith in the Republic.

speaker: QUEEN JAMILLIA
combinedline: The day we stop believing democracy can work is the day we lose it.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Let's pray that day never comes.

speaker: QUEEN JAMILLIA
combinedline: In the meantime, we must consider your own safety.

speaker: SIO BIBBLE
combinedline: What is your suggestion,

speaker: SIO BIBBILE
combinedline: Master Jedi?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Oh, Anakin's not a Jedi yet. He's still a Padawan learner.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: But I was thinking--

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Hold on a minute.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Excuse me.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I was thinking I would stay in the lake country. There are some places up there that are very isolated.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Excuse me. I'm in charge of security here, milady.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: And this is my home. I know it very well. That is why we're here. I think it would be wise if you took advantage of my knowledge in this instance.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Sorry, milady.

speaker: QUEEN JAMILLIA
combinedline: Perfect. It's settled, then.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: There it is, R4, right where it should be. Our missing planet Kamino.

speaker: TAUN WE
combinedline: Master Jedi. The prime minister is expecting you.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I'm expected?

speaker: TAUN WE
combinedline: Of course. He is anxious to meet you. After all these years... we were beginning to think you weren't coming. Now, please, this way.

speaker: TAUN WE
combinedline: May I present Lama Su... prime minister of Kamino. And this is Master Jedi--

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Obi-Wan Kenobi.

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: I trust you're going to enjoy your stay. Please. And now to business. You will be delighted to hear that we are on schedule. 200,000 units are ready... with a million more well on the way.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: That's good news.

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: Please tell your Master Sifo-Dyas... that his order will be met on time.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I'm sorry. Master--

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: Jedi Master Sifo-Dyas is still a leading member of the Jedi Council... is he not?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Master Sifo-Dyas was killed almost ten years ago.

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: Oh, I'm so sorry to hear that. But I'm sure he would have been proud of the army we've built for him.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The army?

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: Yes. A clone army, and I must say, one of the finest we've ever created.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Tell me, Prime Minister... when my master first contacted you about the army... did he say who it was for?

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: Of course he did. This army is for the Republic. But you must be anxious to inspect the units for yourself.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: That's why I'm here.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: We used to come here for school retreat. We would swim to that island every day. I love the water. We used to lie out on the sand and let the sun dry us... and try to guess the names of the birds singing.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I don't like sand. It's coarse and rough and irritating... and it gets everywhere. Not like here. Here, everything is soft... and smooth.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: No. I shouldn't have done that.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm sorry.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Very impressive.

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: I'd hoped you would be pleased. Clones can think creatively. You will find that they are immensely superior to droids. We take great pride in our combat education and training programs. This group was created about five years ago.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You mentioned growth acceleration.

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: Oh,yes, it's essential. Otherwise, a mature clone would take a lifetime to grow. Now we can do it in half the time.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I see.

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: They are totally obedient... taking any order without question. We modified their genetic structure... to make them less independent than the original host.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: And who was the original host?

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: A bounty hunter called Jango Fett.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: And where is this bounty hunter now?

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: Oh, we keep him here. Apart from his pay, which is considerable... Fett demanded only one thing: an unaltered clone for himself. Curious, isn't it?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Unaltered?

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: Pure genetic replication. No tampering with the structure to make it more docile... and no growth acceleration.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I should very much like to meet this Jango Fett.

speaker: TAUN WE
combinedline: I would be very happy to arrange it.

speaker: LAMA SU
combinedline: Magnificent, aren't they?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I don't know.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Sure you do. You just don't want to tell me.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You gonna use one of your Jedi mind tricks on me?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: They only work on the weak-minded.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: All right. I was twelve. His name was Palo. We were both in the Legislative Youth Program. He was a few years older than I. Very cute. Dark, curly hair. Dreamy eyes.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: All right, I get the picture. Whatever happened to him?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I went into public service; he went on to become an artist.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Maybe he was the smart one.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You really don't like politicians, do you?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I like two or three... but I'm not really sure about one of them. I don't think the system works.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: How would you have it work?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: We need a system where the politicians sit down and discuss the problem... agree what's in the best interest of all the people, and then do it.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: That's exactly what we do. The trouble is that people don't always agree.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Well, then they should be made to.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: By whom? Who's gonna make them?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I don't know. Someone.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Of course not me.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: But someone.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Someone wise.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Sounds an awful lot like a dictatorship to me.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Well, if it works.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You're making fun of me.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: No. I'd be much too frightened to tease a senator.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Whoa, whoa. Oh, whoa!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Ani! Ani, are you all right?

speaker: TAUN WE
combinedline: Boba, is your father here?

speaker: BOBA FETT
combinedline: Yep.

speaker: TAUN WE
combinedline: May we see him?

speaker: BOBA FETT
combinedline: Sure.

speaker: BOBA FETT
combinedline: Dad, Taun We's here.

speaker: TAUN WE
combinedline: Jango, welcome back. Was your trip productive?

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Fairly.

speaker: TAUN WE
combinedline: This is Jedi Master Obi-Wan Kenobi. He's come to check on our progress.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Your clones are very impressive. You must be very proud.

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: I'm just a simple man trying to make my way in the universe.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Ever made your way as far into the interior as Coruscant?

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Once or twice.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Recently?

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Possibly.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Then you must know Master Sifo-Dyas.

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Boba, rood eht so-heeck.

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Master who?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Sifo-Dyas. Is he not the Jedi who hired you for this job?

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Never heard of him.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Really?

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: I was recruited by a man called Tyranus on one of the moons of Bogden.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Curious.

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Do you like your army?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I look forward to seeing them in action.

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: They'll do their job well. I'll guarantee that.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Thank you for your time, Jango.

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Always a pleasure to meet a Jedi.

speaker: BOBA FETT
combinedline: What is it, Dad?

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Pack your things. We're leaving.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: And when I got to them, we went into aggressive negotiations.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Thank you.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Aggressive negotiations? What's that?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Uh, well, negotiations with a lightsaber.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Oh.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: If Master Obi-Wan caught me doing this, he'd be very grumpy. From the moment I met you... all those years ago... not a day has gone by when I haven't thought of you. And now that I'm with you again... I'm in agony. The closer I get to you, the worse it gets. The thought of not being with you-- I can't breathe. I'm haunted by the kiss that you should never have given me. My heart is beating... hoping that that kiss will not become a scar. You are in my very soul... tormenting me. What can I do? I will do anything that you ask. If you are suffering as much as I am, please, tell me.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I can't. We can't. It's...just not possible.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Anything is possible, Padme. Listen to me.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: No, you listen. We live in a real world. Come back to it. You're studying to become a Jedi. I'm- I'm a senator. If you follow your thoughts through to conclusion... it'll take us to a place we cannot go... regardless of the way we feel about each other.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Then you do feel something.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I will not let you give up your future for me.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You are asking me to be rational. That is something I know I cannot do. Believe me, I wish that I could just wish away my feelings... but I can't.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I will not give in to this.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Well, you know, it... wouldn't have to be that way. We could keep it a secret.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: We'd be living a lie... one we couldn't keep even if we wanted to. I couldn't do that. Could you, Anakin? Could you live like that?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: No. You're right. It would destroy us.

speaker: TAUN WE
combinedline: Tell your council that the first battalions are ready. And remind them, if they need more troops... it will take more time to grow them.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I won't forget, and thank you.

speaker: TAUN WE
combinedline: Thank you.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: R4! Scramble code five to Coruscant, care of the old folks' home!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I have successfully made contact with the prime minister of Kamino. They are using a bounty hunter named Jango Fett to create a clone army. I have a strong feeling that this bounty hunter... is the assassin we are looking for.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Do you think these cloners are involved in the plot to assassinate Senator Amidala?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: No, Master. There appears to be no motive.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Do not assume anything, Obi-Wan. Clear your mind must be... if you are to discover the real villains behind this plot.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Yes, Master.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: They say Master Sifo-Dyas placed an order for a clone army... at the request of the senate almost ten years ago. I was under the impression he was killed before that. Did the council ever authorize the creation of a clone army?

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: No. Whoever placed that order did not have the authorization of the Jedi Council.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Bring him here. Question him we will.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Yes, Master. I will report back when I have him.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Blind we are if creation of this clone army... we could not see.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: I think it is time we informed the senate... that our ability to use the Force has diminished.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Only the dark lord of the Sith knows of our weakness. If informed the senate is... multiply our adversaries will.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: No. No.

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Anakin, help me.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Mom, no.

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Anakin!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Don't. No. No.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Don't go.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I don't want to disturb you.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Your presence is soothing.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: You had another nightmare last night.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Jedi don't have nightmares.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I heard you.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I saw my mother. She is suffering, Padme. I saw her as clearly as I see you now. She is in pain. I know I'm disobeying my mandate to protect you, Senator... but I have to go. I have to help her.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I'll go with you.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm sorry. I don't have a choice.

speaker: BOBA FETT
combinedline: Dad, look!

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Boba, get on board!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Oh, not good.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Wait right there.

speaker: ROBOT
combinedline: Okey-okey.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: Da wanga!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Chut-chut, Watto. Let me help you with that.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: What? What do you want? Wait! You're a Jedi! Whatever it is, I didn't do it.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm looking for Shmi Skywalker.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: Ani? Little Ani? Nahhh. You are Ani! It is you! You sure sprouted, huh? A Jedi! What do ya know! Hey... maybe you could help with some deadbeats who owe me a lot of money.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: My mother.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: Oh, yeah. Shmi. she's not mine no more. I sold her.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You sold her?

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: Years ago. Sorry, Ani, but you know, business is business, huh? Yeah, I sold her to a moisture farmer named, uh, Lars. At least I think it was Lars. Believe it or not, I heard he freed her and married her! Can ya beat that, eh? Yeah.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Do you know where they are now?

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: Long way from here. Someplace over on the other side of Mos Eisley, I think.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'd like to know.

speaker: WATTO
combinedline: Sure. Absolutely! Let's go look at my records?

speaker: BOBA FETT
combinedline: Dad! I think we're being tracked!

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: He must have put a homing device on our hull. Hang on, son. We'll move into the asteroid field... and we'll have a couple of surprises for him.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Seismic charges! Stand by.

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: He doesn't seem to take a hint, this guy.

speaker: BOBA FETT
combinedline: Watch out! Get him, Dad! Get him! Fire!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Oh, blast! This is why I hate flying!

speaker: BOBA FETT
combinedline: We got him!

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: We'll just have to finish him.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: R4, prepare to jettison the spare part canisters. Fire them now!

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Well, we won't be seeing him again.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Well, R4, I think we've waited long enough. There's an unusual concentration of Federation ships over there, R4.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [Whistles, Beeps ]

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Stay with the ship, R2.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh! Um, uh, hello. How might I be of service? I am C--

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Threepio?

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh-- The maker! Oh, Master Ani! I knew you would return. I knew it!

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: And Miss Padme. Oh, my.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Hello, 3PO.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Bless my circuits!

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: I'm so pleased to see you both.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I've come to see my mother.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh. I think perhaps we'd better go indoors.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Master Owen, might I present two most important visitors.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm Anakin Skywalker.

speaker: OWEN LARS
combinedline: Owen Lars. Uh, this is my girlfriend, Beru.

speaker: BERU
combinedline: Hello.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I'm Padme.

speaker: OWEN LARS
combinedline: I guess I'm your stepbrother. I had a feeling you might show up someday.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Is my mother here?

speaker: CLIEGG LARS
combinedline: No, she's not. Cliegg Lars. Shmi is my wife. We should go inside. We have a lot to talk about.

speaker: CLIEGG LARS
combinedline: It was just before dawn. They came out of nowhere. A hunting party of Tusken Raiders. Your mother had gone out early, like she always did... to pick mushrooms that grow on the vaporators. From the tracks, she was about halfway home... when they took her. Those Tuskens walk like men... but they're vicious, mindless monsters. Thirty of us went out after her. Four of us came back. I'd be out there with them, but after I lost my leg... I just couldn't ride anymore until I heal. I don't want to give up on her... but she's been gone a month. There's little hope she's lasted this long.

speaker: OWEN LARS
combinedline: Where are you going?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: To find my mother.

speaker: CLIEGG LARS
combinedline: Your mother's dead, son. Accept it.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You're gonna have to stay here. These are good people, Padme. You'll be safe.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Anakin--

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I won't be long.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: We must persuade

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: the Commerce Guild... and the Corporate Alliance to sign the treaty.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: What about the senator from Naboo? Is she dead yet? I am not signing your treaty until I have her head on my desk.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: I am a man of my word, Viceroy.

speaker: ALIEN
combinedline: With these new battle droids we've built for you... you'll have the finest army in the galaxy.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: As I explained to you earlier... I am quite convinced that 10,000 more systems... will rally to our cause with your support, gentlemen.

speaker: ALIEN
combinedline: What you are proposing could be construed as treason.

speaker: CYBORG
combinedline: The Techno Union army... is at your disposal, Count.

speaker: ALIEN 2
combinedline: The Banking Clan will sign your treaty.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Good. Very good. Our friends from the Trade Federation have pledged their support... and when their battle droids are combined with yours... we shall have an army greater than any in the galaxy. The Jedi will be overwhelmed. The Republic will agree to any demands we make.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Mom. Mom? Mom?

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Ani? Ani? Is it you?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm here, Mom. You're safe.

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Ani? Ani? Oh, you look so handsome. My son. Oh, my grown-up son. I'm so proud of you, Ani.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I missed you.

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: Now I am complete. I love-

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Stay with me, Mom. Everything--

speaker: SHMI
combinedline: I love-- I-- I love--

speaker: QUI-GON
combinedline: Anakin! Anakin!

speaker: ??? OTHER VOICE
combinedline: No-o-o!

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: What is it?

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Pain, suffering... death I feel. Something terrible has happened. Young Skywalker is in pain. Terrible pain.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The transmitter is working, but we're not receiving a return signal. Coruscant's too far.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: R4, can you boost the power? We'll have to try something else. Maybe we can contact Anakin on Naboo. It's much closer.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin? Anakin, do you copy? This is Obi-Wan Kenobi. Anakin?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: He's not on Naboo, R4. I'm going to try and widen the range. I do hope nothing's happened to him. That's Anakin's tracking signal, all right... but it's coming from Tatooine. What in the blazes is he doing there? I told him to stay on Naboo. We haven't got much time.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin? Anakin, do you copy? This is Obi-Wan Kenobi. Retransmit this message-- Anakin, do you copy? Anakin-- My long-range-- has been knocked out. Retransmit this message to Coruscant.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I brought you something. Are you hungry?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: The shifter broke. Life seems so much simpler when you're fixing things. I'm good at fixing things. Always was. But I couldn't-- Why'd she have to die? Why couldn't I save her? I know I could have!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Sometimes there are things no one can fix. You're not all-powerful, Ani.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Well, I should be! Someday I will be. I will be the most powerful Jedi ever! I promise you. I will even learn to stop people from dying.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Anakin.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: It's all Obi-Wan's fault! He's jealous! He's holding me back!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: What's wrong, Ani?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I-- I killed them. I killed them all. They're dead. Every single one of them. And not just the men... but the women... and the children too. They're like animals, and I slaughtered them like animals! I hate them!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: To be angry is to be human.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm a Jedi. I know I'm better than this.

speaker: CLIEGG LARS
combinedline: I know wherever you are it's become a better place. You were the most loving partner a man could ever have. Good-bye, my darling wife. And thank you.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I wasn't strong enough to save you, Mom. I wasn't strong enough. But I promise I won't fail again. I miss you... so much.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: PADME
combinedline: R2? What are you doing here?

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: It seems that he is carrying a message from an Obi-Wan Kenobi.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Master Ani, does that name mean anything to you?

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: OBI-WAN
addressed: ANAKIN, PADME, YODA, MACE WINDU, JAR JAR, BAIL ORGANA, PALPATINE, MAS AMEDDA
combinedline: Anakin, my long-range transmitter has been knocked out. Retransmit this message to Coruscant. I have tracked the bounty hunter, Jango Fett... to the droid foundries on Geonosis. The Trade Federation is to take delivery of a droid army here... and it is clear that Viceroy Gunray... is behind the assassination attempts on Senator Amidala. The Commerce Guilds and the Corporate Alliance... have both pledged their armies to Count Dooku and are forming a-- Wait. Wait.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: More happening on Geonosis, I feel, than has been revealed.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: I agree.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Anakin, we will deal with Count Dooku. The most important thing for you is to stay where you are. Protect the senator at all costs. That is your first priority.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Understood, Master.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: They'll never get there in time to save him. They have to come halfway across the galaxy. Look. Geonosis is less than a parsec away.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: If he's still alive.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Ani, are you just gonna sit here and let him die? He's your friend, your mentor. He's--

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: He's like my father! But you heard Master Windu. He gave me strict orders to stay here!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: He gave you strict orders to protect me... and I'm going to help Obi-Wan. If you plan to protect me, you'll just have to come along.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: BEEPS THREE TIMES

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: I'm not worried, R2. It's just I've never flown before.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
addressed: PALPATINE, SENATOR ASK AAK, MAS AMEDDA, JAR JAR, YODA, MACE WINDU
combinedline: The Commerce Guilds are preparing for war. There can be no doubt of that.

speaker: PALPATINE
addressed: BAIL ORGANA, SENATOR ASK AAK, MAS AMEDDA, JAR JAR, YODA, MACE WINDU
combinedline: Count Dooku must have made a treaty with them.

speaker: SENATOR ASK AAK
addressed: BAIL ORGANA, PALPATINE, MAS AMEDDA, JAR JAR, YODA, MACE WINDU
combinedline: The debate is over. Now we need that clone army.

speaker: BAIL ORGANA
addressed: PALPATINE, SENATOR ASK AAK, MAS AMEDDA, JAR JAR, YODA, MACE WINDU
combinedline: Unfortunately, the debate is not over. The senate will never approve the use of clones before the separatists attack.

speaker: MAS AMEDDA
addressed: BAIL ORGANA, PALPATINE, SENATOR ASK AAK, JAR JAR, YODA, MACE WINDU
combinedline: This is a crisis. The senate must vote the chancellor emergency powers. He can then approve the creation of an army.

speaker: PALPATINE
addressed: BAIL ORGANA, SENATOR ASK AAK, MAS AMEDDA, JAR JAR, YODA, MACE WINDU
combinedline: But what senator would have the courage to propose such a radical amendment?

speaker: MAS AMEDDA
addressed: BAIL ORGANA, PALPATINE, MAS AMEDDA, JAR JAR, SENATOR ASK AAK, YODA, MACE WINDU
combinedline: If only... Senator Amidala were here.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Traitor.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Oh, no, my friend. This is a mistake, a terrible mistake. They have gone too far. This is madness.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I thought you were the leader here, Dooku.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: This had nothing to do with me, I assure you. I will petition immediately to have you set free.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Well, I hope it doesn't take too long. I have work to do.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: May I ask why a Jedi knight... is all the way out here on Geonosis?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I've been tracking a bounty hunter named Jango Fett. Do you know him?

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: There are no bounty hunters here that I am aware of. The Geonosians don't trust them.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Who can blame them? But he is here, I can assure you.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: It's a great pity that our paths have never crossed before, Obi-Wan. Qui-Gon always spoke very highly of you. I wish he were still alive. I could use his help right now.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Qui-Gon Jinn would never join you.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Don't be so sure, my young Jedi. You forget that he was once my apprentice... just as you were once his. He knew all about the corruption in the senate... but he would never have gone along with it if he had learned the truth as I have.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: The truth?

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: The truth. What if I told you that the Republic... was now under the control of the dark lord of the Sith?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: No, that's not possible. The Jedi would be aware of it.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: The dark side of the Force has clouded their vision, my friend. Hundreds of senators are now under the influence... of a Sith lord called Darth Sidious.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I don't believe you.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: The viceroy of the Trade Federation... was once in league with this Darth Sidious... but he was betrayed ten years ago by the dark lord. He came to me for help. He told me everything. You must join me, Obi-Wan... and together we will destroy the Sith!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I will never join you, Dooku.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: It may be difficult to secure your release.

speaker: JAR JAR
combinedline: It's-a clear desa separatists made a pact... wesa desa Federation du Trade. Senators, ''dellow felagates'' In response to this direct threat to the Republic... mesa propose that the senate... give immediately emergency powers... to the supreme chancellor.

speaker: AUDIENCE
combinedline: Palpatine! Palpatine! Palpatine!

speaker: MAS AMEDDA
combinedline: Order! We shall have order!

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: It is with great reluctance... that I have agreed to this calling. I love democracy. I love the Republic. The power you give me... I will lay down when this crisis has abated. And as my first act with this new authority... I will create a grand army of the Republic... to counter the increasing threats of the separatists.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: It is done, then. I will take what Jedi we have left and go to Geonosis and help Obi-Wan.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Visit I will the cloners on Kamino... and see this army they have created for the Republic.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: See those columns of steam straight ahead? They're exhaust vents of some type.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: That'll do.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Look, whatever happens out there, follow my lead. I'm not interested in getting into a war here. As a member of the senate... maybe I can find a diplomatic solution to this mess.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Don't worry. I've given up trying to argue with you.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Whistling, Beeping ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: My obtuse little friend, if they had needed our help... they would have asked for it. You obviously have a great deal to learn about human behavior.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ] [ Beeping ]

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: For a mechanic... you seem to do an excessive amount of thinking.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: I am programmed to understand humans!

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: What does that mean?'' Oh! That means I am in charge here!

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Raspberries ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Where are you going now?

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: You don't know what's out there. Have you no sense at all?

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh! Idiot! Please wait.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Do you know where you're going?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Wait.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh, my. Oh, oh oh!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Padme!

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh, my goodness! Shut me down! Machines making machines. Huh! How perverse.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh! Calm down, R2.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: I almost fell. You'll get your chance--

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh! I'm scrap. It's a nightmare! Oh, I want to go home! Oh, what did I do to deserve this?

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ] [ Whistling ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Hmm. I wonder what happened to poor little R2. He's always getting himself into trouble. Oops. Oh, no! Oh, I'm so confused.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Oh, not again. Obi-Wan's gonna kill me.

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Don't move, Jedi!

speaker: JANGO FETT
combinedline: Take him away.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Don't be afraid.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I'm not afraid to die. I've been dying a little bit each day since you came back into my life.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What are you talking about?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I love you.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You love me? I thought that we had decided not to fall in love... that we would be forced to live a lie... and that it would destroy our lives.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: I think our lives are about to be destroyed anyway. I truly... deeply love you... and before we die, I want you to know.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I was beginning to wonder if you'd got my message.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I retransmitted it just as you had requested, Master. Then we decided to come and rescue you.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Good job.

speaker: POGGLE THE LESSER
combinedline: Settle down. Settle down. Let the executions begin.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I've got a bad feeling about this.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Just relax. Concentrate.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: What about Padme?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: She seems to be on top of things.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: She can't do that! Shoot her or-- or something!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Jump!

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: This isn't how it's supposed to be!

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: Jango! Finish her off!.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Patience, Viceroy, patience. She will die.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Master Windu, how pleasant of you to join us.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: This party's over.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Brave but foolish, my old Jedi friend. You're impossibly outnumbered.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: I don't think so.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: We'll see.

speaker: ROBOT
combinedline: My legs aren't moving. I must need maintenance.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: What's all this noise? A battle! Oh, there's been some terrible mistake! I'm programmed for etiquette, not destruction!

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Die, Jedi dogs!

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh! What did I say? Oh, dear. I'm terribly sorry about all this.

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Excuse me. I'm trapped. I can't get up.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You call this a diplomatic solution?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: No, I call it aggressive negotiations.

speaker: ROBOT
combinedline: Roger, roger.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: R2, what are you doing here?

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: What are you doing? Oh, stop that! You're going to strain something. My neck! Now where are you taking me?

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh, this is such a drag. Oh, I'm quite beside myself. R2, please be careful! You're singeing my circuits!

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Yes, but is my head on straight?

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Master Windu, you have fought gallantly... worthy of recognition in the archives of the Jedi order. Now it is finished. Surrender, and your lives will be spared.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: We will not be hostages to be bartered, Dooku!

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Then, I'm sorry, old friend.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Look!

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Around the survivors a perimeter create.

speaker: R2D2
combinedline: [ Beeping, Chirping ]

speaker: THREEPIO
combinedline: Oh, I've had the most peculiar dream.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: If Dooku escapes... rally more systems to his cause he will.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Hold on!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Aim right above the fuel cells!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Good call, my young Padawan.

speaker: NUTE
addressed: COUNT DOOKU, POGGLE THE LESSER, RUNE
combinedline: The Jedi have amassed a huge army.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: That doesn't seem possible. How could the Jedi come up with an army so quickly?

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: We must send all available droids into battle.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: There are too many.

speaker: POGGLE THE LESSER
combinedline: Our communications have been jammed.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Pilot, land in that assembly area!

speaker: PILOT
combinedline: Yes, sir.

speaker: COMMANDO CAPTAIN
combinedline: Sir, I have five special commando units awaiting your orders, sir.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: To the forward command center take me.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Attack those Federation starships! Quickly!

speaker: COMMANDO CAPTAIN
combinedline: Master Yoda, all forward positions are advancing.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Very good. Very good.

speaker: NUTE
combinedline: This is not looking good at all!

speaker: RUNE
combinedline: We must get the starships back into space.

speaker: POGGLE THE LESSER
combinedline: We have to order a retreat.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: My master will never allow the Republic... to get away with this treachery.

speaker: POGGLE THE LESSER
combinedline: I'm sending my warriors to hide in the catacombs. The Jedi must not find our designs for the ultimate weapon. If they find out what we are planning to build, we're doomed.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: I will take the designs with me to Coruscant. They will be much safer there with my master.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Concentrate all your fire on the nearest starship.

speaker: COMMANDO CAPTAIN
combinedline: Yes, sir.

speaker: COMMANDO CAPTAIN
combinedline: Move all quadrants to sector 5-1 -5.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Look over there!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: It's Dooku!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Shoot him down!

speaker: COMMANDO CAPTAIN
combinedline: We're out of rockets, sir.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Follow him!

speaker: PADME
combinedline: We're gonna need some help!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: There isn't time! Anakin and I can handle this!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Padme!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Put the ship down!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin! Don't let your personal feelings get in the way! Follow that speeder!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Lower the ship!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I can't take Dooku alone! I need you! If we catch him, we can end this war right now! We have a job to do!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I don't care!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: Put the ship down!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: You will be expelled from the Jedi order!

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I can't leave her!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Come to your senses! What do you think Padme would do were she in your position?

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: She would do her duty.

speaker: COMMANDO CAPTAIN
combinedline: The droid army is in full retreat.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Well done, Commander. Bring me a ship.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: You're gonna pay for all the Jedi that you killed today, Dooku.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: We'll take him together. Go in slowly on the left.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I'm taking him now!

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: No, Anakin! No! No!

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: As you see, my Jedi powers are far beyond yours. Now... back down.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I don't think so.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Master Kenobi, you disappoint me. Yoda holds you in such high esteem. Surely you can do better.

speaker: COMMANDO CAPTAIN
combinedline: Are you all right?

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Uh-huh.

speaker: COMMANDO CAPTAIN
combinedline: We'd better get back to the forward command center.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: No. No. Gather what troops you can. We've got to get to that hangar. Get a transport. Hurry!

speaker: COMMANDO CAPTAIN
combinedline: Right away.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Brave of you, boy. But I would have thought you had learned your lesson.

speaker: ANAKIN
combinedline: I am a slow learner.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Anakin!

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: Master Yoda.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Count Dooku.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: You have interfered with our affairs for the last time.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Powerful you have become, Dooku. The dark side I sense in you.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: I've become more powerful than any Jedi. Even you.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Much to learn you still have.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: It is obvious that this contest cannot be decided by our knowledge of the Force... but by our skills with a lightsaber.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Fought well you have, my old Padawan.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: This is just the beginning.

speaker: PADME
combinedline: Anakin!

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: The Force is with us, Master Sidious.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Welcome home, Lord Tyranus. You have done well.

speaker: COUNT DOOKU
combinedline: I have good news for you, my lord. The war has begun.

speaker: PALPATINE
combinedline: Excellent. Everything is going as planned.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: Do you believe what Count Dooku said... about Sidious controlling the senate? It doesn't feel right.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Joined the dark side Dooku has. Lies, deceit... creating mistrust are his ways now.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Nevertheless, I feel we should keep a closer eye on the senate.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: I agree.

speaker: MACE WINDU
combinedline: Where is your apprentice?

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: On his way to Naboo, escorting Senator Amidala home.

speaker: OBI-WAN
combinedline: I have to admit that without the clones, it would not have been a victory.

speaker: YODA
combinedline: Victory? Victory, you say? Master Obi-Wan, not victory. The shroud of the dark side has fallen. Begun the Clone War has.
